Protocols/XCDYouTubeOperation.html#/c:ob.name: -cancel
Protocols/XCDYouTubeOperation.html#/c:ob.abstract: Cancels the operation. If the operation is already finished, does nothing.

Protocols/XCDYouTubeOperation.html.name: XCDYouTubeOperation
Protocols/XCDYouTubeOperation.html.abstract: The XCDYouTubeOperation protocol is adopted by opaque objects returned by the <-[XCDYouTubeClient getVideoWithIdentifier:completionHandler:]> method.

Enums/XCDLogLevel.html#/c:@E@XCDLogLevel.name: XCDLogLevelError
Enums/XCDLogLevel.html#/c:@E@XCDLogLevel.abstract: Used when an error is produced, e.g. when a <XCDYouTubeVideoOperation> finishes with an error.

Enums/XCDLogLevel.html#/c:@E@XCDLogLevel.name: XCDLogLevelWarning
Enums/XCDLogLevel.html#/c:@E@XCDLogLevel.abstract: Used on unusual conditions that may eventually lead to an error.

Enums/XCDLogLevel.html#/c:@E@XCDLogLevel.name: XCDLogLevelInfo
Enums/XCDLogLevel.html#/c:@E@XCDLogLevel.abstract: Used when logging normal operational information, e.g. when a <XCDYouTubeVideoOperation> starts, is cancelled or finishes.

Enums/XCDLogLevel.html#/c:@E@XCDLogLevel.name: XCDLogLevelDebug
Enums/XCDLogLevel.html#/c:@E@XCDLogLevel.abstract: Used throughout a <XCDYouTubeVideoOperation> for debugging purpose, e.g. for HTTP requests.

Enums/XCDLogLevel.html#/c:@E@XCDLogLevel.name: XCDLogLevelVerbose
Enums/XCDLogLevel.html#/c:@E@XCDLogLevel.abstract: Used to report large amount of information, e.g. full HTTP responses.

Enums/XCDYouTubeErrorCode.html#/c:@E@XCD.name: XCDYouTubeErrorNoStreamAvailable
Enums/XCDYouTubeErrorCode.html#/c:@E@XCD.abstract: Returned when no suitable video stream is available. This can occur due to various reason such as:

Enums/XCDYouTubeErrorCode.html#/c:@E@XCD.name: XCDYouTubeErrorNetwork
Enums/XCDYouTubeErrorCode.html#/c:@E@XCD.abstract: Returned when a network error occurs. See NSUnderlyingErrorKey in the userInfo dictionary for more information.

Enums/XCDYouTubeErrorCode.html#/c:@E@XCD.name: XCDYouTubeErrorEmptyResponse
Enums/XCDYouTubeErrorCode.html#/c:@E@XCD.abstract: Returned when an empty response is returned. This may indicate that YouTube has blocked requests from your IP address because of overuse.

Enums/XCDYouTubeErrorCode.html#/c:@E@XCD.name: XCDYouTubeErrorInvalidVideoIdentifier
Enums/XCDYouTubeErrorCode.html#/c:@E@XCD.abstract: Previously returned when the given video identifier string is invalid.

Enums/XCDYouTubeErrorCode.html#/c:@E@XCD.name: XCDYouTubeErrorRemovedVideo
Enums/XCDYouTubeErrorCode.html#/c:@E@XCD.abstract: Previously returned when the video was removed as a violation of YouTube’s policy or when the video did not exist.

Enums/XCDYouTubeErrorCode.html#/c:@E@XCD.name: XCDYouTubeErrorRestrictedPlayback
Enums/XCDYouTubeErrorCode.html#/c:@E@XCD.abstract: Previously returned when the video is not playable because of legal reasons or when the video is private.

Enums/XCDYouTubeErrorCode.html.name: XCDYouTubeErrorCode
Enums/XCDYouTubeErrorCode.html.abstract: These values are returned as the error code property of an NSError object with the domain XCDYouTubeVideoErrorDomain.

Enums/XCDLogLevel.html.name: XCDLogLevel
Enums/XCDLogLevel.html.abstract: The log levels, closely mirroring the log levels of CocoaLumberjack.

Enums/XCDYouTubeVideoQuality.html.name: XCDYouTubeVideoQuality
Enums/XCDYouTubeVideoQuality.html.abstract: The quality of YouTube videos. These values are used as keys in the <[XCDYouTubeVideo streamURLs]> property.

Constants.html#/c:@XCDYouTubeAllowedCoun.name: XCDYouTubeAllowedCountriesUserInfoKey
Constants.html#/c:@XCDYouTubeAllowedCoun.abstract: A key that may be present in the error’s userInfo dictionary when the error code is XCDYouTubeErrorNoStreamAvailable.

Constants.html#/c:@XCDYouTubeVideoQualit.name: XCDYouTubeVideoQualityHTTPLiveStreaming
Constants.html#/c:@XCDYouTubeVideoQualit.abstract: Used as a key in the streamURLs property of the XCDYouTubeVideo class for live videos.

Constants.html#/c:@XCDYouTubeVideoPlayer.name: XCDYouTubeVideoPlayerViewControllerDidReceiveVideoNotification
Constants.html#/c:@XCDYouTubeVideoPlayer.abstract: Posted when the video player has received the video information. The object of the notification is the XCDYouTubeVideoPlayerViewController instance. The userInfo dictionary contains the XCDYouTubeVideo object.

Constants.html#/c:@XCDYouTubeVideoUserIn.name: XCDYouTubeVideoUserInfoKey
Constants.html#/c:@XCDYouTubeVideoUserIn.abstract: The key for the XCDYouTubeVideo object in the user info dictionary of XCDYouTubeVideoPlayerViewControllerDidReceiveVideoNotification.

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoQueryOperation.ht.name: -initWithVideo:cookies:
Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoQueryOperation.ht.abstract: Initializes a video query operation with the specified video and cookies.

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoQueryOperation.ht.name: video
Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoQueryOperation.ht.abstract: The video object that the operation initialized initialized with.

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoQueryOperation.ht.name: cookies
Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoQueryOperation.ht.abstract: The array of NSHTTPCookie objects passed during initialization.

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoQueryOperation.ht.name: error
Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoQueryOperation.ht.abstract: Returns an error of the XCDYouTubeVideoErrorDomain domain if the operation failed or nil if it succeeded. The operation will only return an error if no stream URL is reachable (error code: XCDYouTubeErrorNoStreamAvailable). Also, this returns nil if the operation is not yet finished or if it was canceled.

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoPlayerViewControl.name: preferredVideoQualities
Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoPlayerViewControl.abstract: The preferred order for the quality of the video to play. Plays the first match when multiple video streams are available.

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoOperation.html#/c.name: video

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).name: author

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).name: thumbnailURLs
Classes/XCDYouTubeVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).abstract: An array of thumbnail URLs for an images of different sizes. Ordered from smaller to bigger.

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).abstract: A thumbnail URL for an image of small size, i.e. 120×90. May be nil.

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).name: smallThumbnailURL
Classes/XCDYouTubeVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).abstract: A thumbnail URL for an image of small size, i.e. 120×90. May be nil.

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).name: mediumThumbnailURL
Classes/XCDYouTubeVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).abstract: A thumbnail URL for an image of medium size, i.e. 320×180, 480×360 or 640×480. May be nil.

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).name: largeThumbnailURL
Classes/XCDYouTubeVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).abstract: A thumbnail URL for an image of large size, i.e. 1'280×720 or 1'980×1'080. May be nil.

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).name: streamURL
Classes/XCDYouTubeVideo.html#/c:objc(cs).abstract: A streamURL that is compatible on Apple devices (can be nil)

Classes/XCDYouTubeClient.html.name: XCDYouTubeClient
Classes/XCDYouTubeClient.html.abstract: The XCDYouTubeClient class is responsible for interacting with the YouTube API. Given a YouTube video identifier, you will get video information with the <-getVideoWithIdentifier:completionHandler:> method.

Classes/XCDYouTubeLogger.html.name: XCDYouTubeLogger
Classes/XCDYouTubeLogger.html.abstract: You can use the XCDYouTubeLogger class to configure how the XCDYouTubeKit framework emits logs.

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideo.html.name: XCDYouTubeVideo
Classes/XCDYouTubeVideo.html.abstract: Represents a YouTube video. Use the <-[XCDYouTubeClient getVideoWithIdentifier:completionHandler:]> method to obtain a XCDYouTubeVideo object.

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoOperation.html.name: XCDYouTubeVideoOperation
Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoOperation.html.abstract: XCDYouTubeVideoOperation is a subclass of NSOperation that connects to the YouTube API and parse the response.

Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoQueryOperation.ht.name: XCDYouTubeVideoQueryOperation
Classes/XCDYouTubeVideoQueryOperation.ht.abstract: XCDYouTubeVideoQueryOperation is a subclass of NSOperation that check to see if the streamURLs in a XCDYouTubeVideo object is reachable (i.e. does not contain any HTTP errors). This operation will only run on a background queue, starting this operation on the main thread will raise an assertion.
